entries.meaning: An amount produced during a specified period; output or turnout

verbs.description: outturn (third-person singular simple present outturns, present participle outturning, simple past and past participle outturned)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To surpass in turning; to turn better than.
examples: “Sometimes your enemy will have a plane that can outturn yours and outclimb you, but you can suck him right into a trap and your wingman can take him out,” Tommy explained.
